{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Do not require publication of full accounts for small/micro businesses",
        "additional_details": "The proposed changes to UK Company Law could mean:\r\n \r\n- Small businesses will struggle to obtain credit to grow\r\n- Small businesses will have less power in tender processes\r\n- Employees will be able to make assumptions about their pay\r\n- Customers bullying small businesses into cheaper rates/favourable payment terms knowing their business is a substantial % of their revenue\r\n- That for a sole director company this will be akin to having their payslips available for anyone to look up",
        "background": "We believe the option to file abridged accounts should continue to be available to small/micro entities. \r\n \r\nWhen a company is small/micro we believe there is no benefit to commercially sensitive information, such as the profit and loss account, to be made public.",
